metadata.name: Tranquil Place
metadata.description:
Out on a limb  
as calm as the sea breeze  
hair fluttering in the wind  
in quest of the freedom within

The blue frothy waves  
pounding the rocks  
building up a poetic echo  
she tried to take in

The waves of warmth  
travelling across the body  
through the sand  
beneath her feet

A knot in the chest  
behind those weary eyes  
an emotional turmoil  
trickled down her cheeks

Out of the blue  
a stronger wind blew  
felt like a blow  
against her soft supple skin

Swiftly drove  
towards the raging sea  
to drown in all  
her misery and agony

The starving sea was satisfied  
the furious waves were at peace  
the body in symmetrical harmony  
with the ocean's waves streamed

The parched spirit was now content  
as sorrows set her soul free  
the sun was the witness  
of this tranquility by the sea
